    Command daemon round 15 â€” fix timeout mismatch causing circuit breaker trips
    
    The daemon used 30s/300s timeouts but TypeScript only waited 10s+10s=20s total,
    causing premature timeouts that tripped the circuit breaker and blocked all
    subsequent bash commands. The fix makes the daemon the single source of truth:
    it reports its timeout_ms in the ack, and TypeScript adapts.
    
    - Daemon: parse optional `timeout` field from execute request, clamp to [1s, 600s]
    - Daemon: include `timeout_ms` in ack response so TypeScript knows how long to wait
    - TypeScript: post-ack timer reads `timeout_ms` from ack, uses `timeout_ms + 15s` buffer
    - TypeScript: BashToolHandler parses `--timeout N` from command, strips before execution
    - TypeScript: clamp `--timeout` to user-configurable `bashMaxTimeout` setting (default 120s)
    - Tool description: document `--timeout N` universal flag, remove unimplemented `--dry-run`
    
    By file:
    - command-daemon/src/protocol.c: send_ack includes timeout_ms, handle_execute parses timeout
    - src/services/command/CommandClient.ts: execute() accepts timeoutSeconds, dynamic post-ack timer
    - src/core/task/tools/handlers/BashToolHandler.ts: --timeout parsing and maxTimeout clamping
    - src/core/prompts/system-prompt/tools/bash.ts: document --timeout in universal flags
    - src/shared/storage/state-keys.ts: add bashMaxTimeout setting (default 120s)

